    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "30. If there be laid on him a sum of money, &c.—Blood fines are common among the Arabs as they were once general throughout the East. This is the only case where a money compensation, instead of capital punishment, was expressly allowed in the Mosaic law.   ",
